A classified <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">British</ENAMEX> document revealed that <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Britain</ENAMEX> had considered implementing a plan that would have changed the course of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOC">Nile</ENAMEX> in order to put pressure on former President <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gamal Abdel Nasser</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">1956</ENAMEX> to relent on his decision to nationalize <ENAMEX TYPE="LOC">the Suez Canal</ENAMEX> .
